## 6. Monotonic Stack Patterns
| Pattern | Stack Invariant | Use Case |
|---------|----------------|----------|
| Monotonic decreasing | Stack top >= current | Next greater element |
| Monotonic increasing | Stack top <= current | Next smaller element |
| Index-based | Store indices not values | Width calculations |

## 7. Gotchas
- `array.shift()` is O(n) in JS — use index pointer or proper deque
- Monotonic stack: pop WHILE condition holds, then push
- Min Stack: push to min stack even if same value (push min of val and current min)
- BFS: mark visited BEFORE enqueuing (not after dequeuing) to avoid re-enqueue
- For sliding window maximum, use a **deque** storing indices, not a stack

